    {
      "id": "9a64f349_f0a1d2a4",
      "file_path": "src/main/resources/application.yml",
      "patchset_number": 12,
      "line": 58,
      "message": "These are key/value de-serializer that catches exceptions to prevent error scenarios like consumption-block, offset not moving, re-try consuming, and many more.  If the delegate fails to deserialize the record content, the ErrorHandlingDeserializer returns a null value. The record is not passed to the listener. Thus, consumptions can continue while it handles the errors. If no error, key/value delegate.class do its job.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 8063,
        "name": "Halil Cakal",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "halil.cakal@est.tech",
        "username": "halil.cakal"
      },
      "updated": "2023-03-24 11:48:40.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "c9aad553_76be86c8",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "3d9ad724_a61c3933",
      "file_path": "src/main/resources/application.yml",
      "patchset_number": 12,
      "line": 70,
      "message": "Yes, in SubscriptionEventForwarder.java, it has been implemented like eventsPublisher.publishEvent(DMI_AVC_SUBSCRIPTION_TOPIC_PREFIX + dmiName, eventKey, subscriptionEvent). However, dmiName is extracted in run-time. Thus, I have given this topic name having only DMI_AVC_SUBSCRIPTION_TOPIC_PREFIX. Any better solution for this problem is welcome. I can change this config accordingly.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 8063,
        "name": "Halil Cakal",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "halil.cakal@est.tech",
        "username": "halil.cakal"
      },
      "updated": "2023-03-24 11:48:40.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "51dce23a_6370762e",
      "unresolved": true
    },
